<h2> Linear Signals and Systems </h2>
<p><em>Undergraduate course, Electrical and Computer Engineering, <strong>Rutgers University, 2019</strong> </em></p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/mwrf_waveforms.png" alt="Waveforms" class="img-responsive" style="width:100%; height:auto; border-radius:0.375em; display:block; max-height:300px" />
<em style="padding-left:2em"><a href="https://www.mwrf.com/technologies/systems/article/21848973/comparing-narrowband-and-wideband-channels">Artistic Impression</a> of Electro-Magnetic signals</em></p>

<p>Had a great time teaching this course with Dr. Sarwate. We covered basic Signals/Signals, Fourier Transforms, Laplace Transforms and Z-Transforms.</p>

